startup dhcp
go to dashboard
add roles and features
select role based or feature based installation
select server from server pool
select dns and dhcp
click through and install

Go to DHCP in server manager
right click the server and select DHCP MANAGER
right click ipv4 and select new scope
name and describe the scope: select next
enter starting and ending range of the ip adresses u want to get allocated and subnet mask
add exlusion ranges if u want to
select for how long the ip adress will last
select dafault gateway if u want one
skip skip skip skip skip
finish
range has been created

how to create reserved ip addresses 
go to ipv4 in dhcp manager
go to scope
go to reserved
right click and select new reservation
create the new reservation fill in ip address and mac address name etc.
done
